>[Question]
>what's the name of the Z axis( x=abssisa, y=ordinate and z=--?)
>
>[Difficulty]
>
>
>[Thoughts]
>

There is no name for the z coordinate of a point, other than "z".

The terms abscissa and ordinate are very old, and apply only to plane 
coordinate geometry.

See this page, which I found by searching Dr. Math for "abscissa 
ordinate":

  Terms of the Cartesian Coordinates
  http://mathforum.org/library/drmath/view/52563.html

If you have any further questions, feel free to write back.


- Doctor Peterson, The Math Forum
  <http://mathforum.org/dr.math/>

